Setting Up & Initialization:

git init: Creates a new Git repository in the current directory.
git clone <URL>: Clones an existing Git repository from a remote URL to your local machine.
git config [key] [value]: Sets global or local configuration options (e.g., username, email).

Tracking Changes:

git status: Shows the current status of tracked and untracked files in your repository.
git add <file>: Adds a specific file to the staging area for the next commit.
git add .: Adds all tracked files in the current directory to the staging area.

Committing Changes:

git commit -m "<message>": Commits the staged changes with a descriptive message.

Branching & Merging:

git branch: Shows a list of existing branches in your repository.
git checkout -b <branch_name>: Creates and switches to a new branch.
git checkout <branch_name>: Switches to an existing branch.
git merge <branch_name>: Merges the changes from another branch into your current branch.

Viewing History:

git log: Shows the commit history of your repository.
git show <commit_hash>: Shows the details of a specific commit.
